<html>
<head>
<title>
A Decade of Success
</title>
<body bgcolor="fffffffff">
<h2>A Decade of Success In Reducing Alcohol Abuse</h2>
<img src="a.gif" alt="a">lcohol abuse and underage drinking remain very serious challenges, but
significant progress is being made in fighting these problems.<p>
All leading indicators of alcohol abuse, including underage drinking, have shown steady
improvement because of factors, such as the combined education and awareness efforts of
industry, private organizations and government combined with tougher laws and stricter
enforcement.  The declines have been especially dramatic  in underage drinking and drunk
driving.
<ul><A HREF="DECADE.HTM"><IMG SRC="PENCIL.GIF">Underage Drinking Is Decreasing</a><BR>
<A HREF="PEN2.HTM"><IMG SRC="PENCIL.GIF">Drunk Driving Accidents Are Declining</a><br>
<A HREF="TARGET.HTM"><IMG SRC="PENCIL.GIF">Targeted Ennforcement Will Stop Many Remaining Drunk Drivers</a><BR>
<A HREF="MESSAGE.HTM"><IMG SRC="PENCIL.GIF">Responsible Drinking Messages Are Effective</a>
</UL><hr>
<font size=2><I>Four recent polls do a good job of measuring public knowledge about alcohol. The first, conducted in 1990 by Survey Design and Analysis for the federal government's National Institute on Alcohol Abuse and Alcoholism, is based on a random national survey of 2,000 adults. The second, a 1991 survey by the Roper Organization, focused on 1,066 persons 21-years-old and older. The third, a random sample of 738 persons between the ages of 14 and 20, was conducted by the Roper Organization in late 1991. And the fourth, a weighted national sample of 956 students in grades in grades 7 through 12, was reported by the U.S. Department of Health and Human Services in 1991.
</I></font><center><img src="main.gif"></center>
<img src="1.gif"><img src="space.gif" height=1 width=5>Drinking During Pregnancy May Cause Birth Defects<br>
<img src="2.gif"><img src="space.gif" height=1 width=5>Drinking Impairs the Ability to Drive or Operate Heavy Machinery<br>
<img src="3.gif"><img src="space.gif" height=1 width=5>Alcohol Can Be Hazardous If You Use Certain Over-The-Counter, Prescription or Illegal Drugs<br>
<img src="4.gif"><img src="space.gif" height=1 width=5>Alcohol May Become Addictive<br>
<img src="5.gif"><img src="space.gif" height=1 width=5>It Is Illegal For Persons Under 21 To Purchase Alcoholic Beverages<BR>
<HR>
<center><font size=2>
