<html><head><title>Alcohol Research</title></head><body bgcolor="#ffffff"><center><img src="Research.gif"><p></center><i>A major factor in meeting the challenge of alcohol abuse is learning about the problem. Who abuses alcohol? Why? What are its effects, both physical and social? By supporting research at major institutions, America's brewers are helping answer these and other important questions.</i><p><center><table width="85%"><tr><td><ul><li><b>Abstracts & Reviews in Alcohol, Drugs & Driving from UCLA's Alcohol Research Center</B><p>This quarterly research journal, which details the latest information on alcohol abuse, is sent to alcohol researchers worldwide and is partially funded by the brewing industry.<p><li><B>Alcoholic Beverage Medical Research Foundation (ABMRF)</B><p>American and Canadian brewers have provided $16 million to ABMRF, which funds medical and social science research on alcohol issues at institutions through the United States and Canada.</ul></table></center><p>
