<title>BICAF</title>
</head>

<BODY BACKGROUND="rock.GIF" bgcolor="#ffffff">

<IMG SRC="bicaf.gif"><h2>BICAF Grants</h2>
<p>
<h3>Who is Eligible For A BICAF Grant</h3>
<b>
Organizations eligible for Beer Institute Community Assistance Fund (BICAF) grants are qualified community-based, nonprofit organizations whose primary purpose or objective is to combat underage substance abuse through education and prevention programs.
<p>
For maximum effect, BICAF has closely tailored its eligibility requirements. Individuals, political organizations and one-time evens are ineligible for grants. In addition, specific activities are restricted from receiving grants as well. No funding will be provided for capital campaigns; travel or seminar registration; treatment of drug or alcohol-related illness; research; endowments; general operating budgets; or debt reduction.</b>
<hr>
<center><A HREF="form.htm"><strong>Apply For A BICAF Grant</strong></a><p></center>
