	<HEAD>
		<TITLE>The Clarke Institute: Current Events: 1997 Chinese New Year's Dinner</TITLE>
		<LINK REV="made" HREF="mailto:dave@thom.com">
	</HEAD>

	<BODY BACKGROUND="../images/dinner_logo.gif" TEXT="#000000"
		  LINK="#FF9900" ALINK="#FFFFFF" VLINK="#000000">
		<TABLE WIDTH=600 BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR VALIGN=TOP><TD COLSPAN=3>
			<H1><IMG ALT="Current Events" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=169
					 SRC="../images/current_events_h.gif"></H1></TR>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=170 HEIGHT=20>
					   <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=345 HEIGHT=20>			
					   <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD COLSPAN=3><P ALIGN=CENTER><B><IMG ALT="[Photo]"
			SRC="../images/dinner_photo.gif" WIDTH=289 HEIGHT=214></B></P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P><B><IMG ALT="1997 Chinese New Year's Dinner"
			SRC="../images/dinner.gif" WIDTH=302 HEIGHT=26></B></P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P><B>In Celebration of the Year of the Ox</B></P>
			
			<P>Each year, The Clarke Institute of Psychiatry Foundation
			presents its annual dinner in celebration of the Chinese New
			Year. The event consists of a traditional lion dance
			followed by a multi-course Chinese dinner, door prizes and
			raffle.</P>
			
			<P>This year's dinner -- in celebration of the Year of the
			Ox -- is tentatively scheduled for February 19, 1997 at the
			Lai Wah Heen restaurant in the Metropolitan Hotel in
			Toronto. Tickets for the dinner at $138 and raffle tickets
			will be available from the Foundation office (phone:
			416-979-6909, fax: 979-6910) in December, 1996.</P>
			
			<P>With support from the community, the event seeks to raise
			about $40,000 which will benefit The Clarke's Culture,
			Community and Health Studies Program and its efforts to make
			the healthcare system more accessible for immigrants,
			refugees and others whose culture and language may reduce
			the accessibility and effectiveness of mental healthcare
			services.</P>
			
			<P>The dinner is open to all members of the community and is
			attended by people from Chinese, Asian and other
			communities, politicians, business executives, Clarke staff
			and others who support improved delivery and access to
			mental healthcare for Canadians from a variety of ethnic
			backgrounds.</P>
			
			<P><B>Goals:</B></P>
			
			<UL>
				<LI>Raise funds to support The Clarke's Culture, Community and Health Studies Program;
				<LI>Increase awareness of The Clarke and its programs to ethno-cultural groups, particularly the Chinese community;
				<LI>Destigmatize mental illness so that members of ethno-cultural communities who suffer from mental illness will be more willing to come forward for treatment.
			</UL>
			
			<P>Corporate sponsorship opportunities for the Chinese New
			Year 's Dinner are available by calling The Clarke
			Foundation at (416) 979-6909.</P>


		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD COLSPAN=3><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=30>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD><P ALIGN=RIGHT>
				<A HREF="../contents.html"><IMG ALT="*" SRC="../images/back_button_wt.gif"
					WIDTH=154 HEIGHT=58 BORDER=0 HSPACE=8></A></P>
			<TD><P><I><A HREF="../contents.html">Back to Main Contents</A></I></P>
		</TABLE>
	</BODY>
</HTML>
