	<HEAD>
		<TITLE>The Clarke Institute: Current Events: Child Psychiatry for Pediatricians</TITLE>
		<LINK REV="made" HREF="mailto:dave@thom.com">
	</HEAD>

	<BODY BACKGROUND="../images/dinner_logo.gif" TEXT="#000000"
		  LINK="#FF9900" ALINK="#FFFFFF" VLINK="#000000">
		<TABLE WIDTH=600 BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR VALIGN=TOP><TD COLSPAN=3>
			<H1><IMG ALT="Current Events" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=169
					 SRC="../images/current_events_h.gif"></H1></TR>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=170 HEIGHT=20>
					   <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=345 HEIGHT=20>			
					   <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P><B><IMG ALT="Child Psychiatry for Pediatricians"
			SRC="../images/child_psych_ped.gif" WIDTH=302 HEIGHT=26></B></P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P>An Evening Seminar Series<BR>
			January - June 1997<BR>
			6:30 - 8:30 pm</P>
			
			<P>Presented by<BR>
			The Clarke Institute of Psychiatry<BR>
			Child and Family Studies Center<BR>
			and the University of Toronto</P>
			
			<P>The Clarke Institute of Psychiatry<BR>
			250 College Street<BR>
			Toronto, Ontario M5T 1R8</P>
			
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=170 HEIGHT=20>
					   <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=345 HEIGHT=20>			
					   <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P><B>Child Psychiatry for Pediatricians</B></P>
			
			<P>This eight-session seminar series is designed to increase
			Pediatricians' knowledge and skills in identifying,
			diagnosing, treating and referring children with psychiatric
			disorders. The series will include both didactic
			presentations and case discussions.</P>
			
			<P>Participants will augment their understanding of the
			prevalence, etiology, course and treatment of child
			psychiatric disorders. Special attention will be given to
			improving assessment and intervention skills with a view to
			expanding the clinician's capacity to deal with emotional
			and behavioural problems in children.</P>
			
			<P>Participants will be invited to present their own cases for
			group discussion. Participants will receive bound copies of
			key articles in each topic area.</P>
			
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=170 HEIGHT=20>
					   <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=345 HEIGHT=20>			
					   <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P><B>Accreditation</B></P>
			
			<P>Pending application for MOCOMP credits for the Royal College
			of Physicians and Surgeons of Canada.</P>
			
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=170 HEIGHT=20>
					   <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=345 HEIGHT=20>			
					   <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P><B>Program Calendar</B></P>
			
			<HR>
			
			<P>January 14, 1997</P>
			
			<P><I>Principles of Assessment and Interviewing</I><BR>
			Drs. T. Barankin / J. Beitchman</P>
			
			<HR>
			
			<P>January 28, 1997</P>
			
			<P><I>Disruptive Behavioural Disorders: ADHD and Firesetting</I><BR>
			Drs. U. Jain / M. Hanson</P>
			
			<HR>
			
			<P>February 11, 1997</P>
			
			<P><I>Disruptive Behavioural Disorders: Oppositional defiant and conduct disorders</I><BR>
			Drs. J. Beitchman / R. Stirtzinger</P>
			
			<HR>
			
			<P>March 25, 1997</P>
			
			<P><I>Developmental Disorders: Learning disabilities, autism, PDD</I><BR>
			Drs. J. Beitchman / L. Sloman</P>
			
			<HR>
			
			<P>April 8, 1997</P>
			
			<P><I>Adolescent Issues</I><BR>
			Drs. Korenblum / S. Shapiro</P>
			
			<HR>
			
			<P>May 13, 1997</P>
			
			<P><I>Depression and Anxiety Disorders</I><BR>
			Drs. Barankin / D. Schachter</P>
			
			<HR>
			
			<P>June 3, 1997</P>
			
			<P><I>Family Issues: Divorce, death, violence and discord, principles of family therapy</I><BR>
			Drs. E. Hood / L. Sloman</P>
			
			<HR>
			
			<P>June 17, 1997</P>
			
			<P><I>Principles of Pediatric Psychopharmacology and Therapies</I><BR>
			Drs. D. Schachter / U. Jain</P>
			
			<HR>
			
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=170 HEIGHT=20>
					   <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=345 HEIGHT=20>			
					   <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P><B>Organizing Committee</B></P>
			
			<P>The Child Psychiatry for Pediatricians Seminar Series is
			hosted by the Child and Family Studies Center of The Clarke
			Institute of Psychiatry and the Department of Psychiatry at
			the University of Toronto. Chaired by Dr. Tatyana Barankin,
			Head of the Center's Clinic for Children at Risk, and
			Assistant Professor of Psychiatry at the University of
			Toronto, the Organizing Committee includes: Dr. Joseph
			Beitchman, Head, Child and Family Studies Center and
			Professor of Psychiatry and Epidemiology, University of
			Toronto; Dr. Bruce Ferguson, Vice-President and Director of
			Education, Head, Department of Psychology, Clarke Institute
			of Psychiatry, and Professor of Psychiatry and Psychology,
			University of Toronto; Dr. Umesh Jain, Head, Children's
			Medication Clinic, Clarke Institute of Psychiatry and
			Assistant Professor of Psychiatry, University of Toronto;
			Dr. Debbie Schachter, Head, Assessment Clinic, Child and
			Family Studies Center, Clarke Institute of Psychiatry and
			Assistant Professor of Psychiatry, University of Toronto;
			and Dr. A. Saksznajder, a community pediatrician.</P>
			
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=170 HEIGHT=20>
					   <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=345 HEIGHT=20>			
					   <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P><B>Registration Information</B></P>
			
			<P>Registration fee: $ 500.00</P>
			
			<P><I>Refunds:</I></BR>
			A $50.00 handling fee will be deducted upon cancellation.</BR>
			Refund requests must be received in writing by January 1, 1997.</P>
			
			<P>Limited enrollment.</BR>
			Registration fee includes a light supper.</BR>
			Full payment must accompany registration form.</BR>
			Cheques, money orders, Visa and MasterCard will be accepted.</BR>
			Make cheques payable to: Clarke Institute of Psychiatry</P>
			
