		This HTML document was marked up by David Veldhuizen
		of HTM Interactive <http://www.thom.com/> or <dave@thom.com>
		Copyright 1996; all rights reserved.
	 -->

	<HEAD>
		<TITLE>The Clarke Institute: About Mental Illness in Canada</TITLE>
		<LINK REV="made" HREF="mailto:dave@thom.com">
	</HEAD>

	<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#CC6600" ALINK="#FFFFFF" VLINK="#000000">
		<TABLE WIDTH=600 BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR VALIGN=TOP><TD COLSPAN=3>
			<IMG SRC="../images/about_mental_illness_h.gif" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=169
				 ALT="About Mental Illness in Canada">

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=170 HEIGHT=30>
					   <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=345 HEIGHT=30>			
					   <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=30>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P><B>Mental Illness Statistics</B></P>
			
			<P>Recent survey data indicate that 20% of Canada's adult
			population suffered from a mental disorder or drug abuse
			within the past year. Schizophrenia affects over 200 000
			Canadians. Major depression and manic depression affect 36%
			of Canadians and anxiety disorders double that number. At
			least 25% of the medically ill have a treatable psychiatric
			disorder.</P>
			
			<P>The costs of mental illness are immense. For example,
			approximately one-quarter of all hospital days reported in
			Canada are for in-patient management of mental disorders.
			Furthermore, only 20-25% of the total costs of schizophrenia
			and depression to society are direct treatment costs; the
			remaining 75-80% of costs are incurred due to lost social
			and economic productivity. In the case of children, if
			effective interventions are not obtained, the mental, social
			and economic burden of suffering can continue throughout
			their lifetime. But according to the Ontario Child Health
			Study, though almost 20% of Ontario's children need care,
			only one in six is receiving it.</P>
			
			<P>Despite the enormous cost of mental illness, our society
			still spends relatively little to research its causes and
			treatments. Current research expenditures represent only a
			few dollars per patient while by contrast in many physical
			illnesses the comparable figure is over $1 000.00 per
			patient.

		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD COLSPAN=3><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=30>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD><P ALIGN=RIGHT>
				<A HREF="../contents.html"><IMG ALT="*" SRC="../images/back_button_wt.gif"
					WIDTH=154 HEIGHT=58 BORDER=0 HSPACE=8></A></P>
			<TD><P><I><A HREF="../contents.html">Back to Main Contents</A></I></P>
		</TABLE>
	</BODY>
</HTML>
</DOC>
