		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG ALT="*" SRC="../images/bullet_wt_sm.gif" ALIGN=ABSBORROM WIDTH=6 HEIGHT=6 HSPACE=4>
			<TD><A HREF="#education_at_the_clarke">Education at The Clarke</A>
			<TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG ALT="*" SRC="../images/bullet_wt_sm.gif" ALIGN=ABSBORROM WIDTH=6 HEIGHT=6 HSPACE=4>
			<TD><A HREF="#continuing_education">Continuing Education of Mental Health Professionals</A>
			<TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG ALT="*" SRC="../images/bullet_wt_sm.gif" ALIGN=ABSBORROM WIDTH=6 HEIGHT=6 HSPACE=4>
			<TD><A HREF="#public_education">Public Education</A>
			<TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG ALT="*" SRC="../images/bullet_wt_sm.gif" ALIGN=ABSBORROM WIDTH=6 HEIGHT=6 HSPACE=4>
			<TD><A HREF="#staff_education">Staff Education</A>
			<TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG ALT="*" SRC="../images/bullet_wt_sm.gif" ALIGN=ABSBORROM WIDTH=6 HEIGHT=6 HSPACE=4>
			<TD><A HREF="practicums.html">Practicums at The Clarke</A>
			<TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG ALT="*" SRC="../images/bullet_wt_sm.gif" ALIGN=ABSBORROM WIDTH=6 HEIGHT=6 HSPACE=4>
			<TD><A HREF="internships.html">Internships at The Clarke</A>
			<TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>


		<TR VALIGN=BOTTOM><TD>
			<TD><P><A NAME="education_at_the_clarke"><IMG ALT="Education at The Clarke" SRC="../images/education_at_the_clarke.gif" WIDTH=302 HEIGHT=26></A></P>
			<TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=60>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P>Education is integral to our tripartite mission and
			is a major focus of activity at The Clarke Institute. The
			Clarke is committed to training students in all the major
			mental health disciplines, providing ongoing continuing
			education to mental health professionals and responding to
			the need for public education. We also support the
			professional and personal development of our own staff.</P>
			
		<TR VALIGN=BOTTOM><TD>
			<TD><P><IMG ALT="Training in the Mental Health Disciplines" SRC="../images/training_in_disciplines.gif" WIDTH=302 HEIGHT=26></P>
			<TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=60>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P>Our special relationship with the University of Toronto
			makes us a very active teaching centre. Each year over 300
			students are involved in training at The Clarke. We offer
			formal programs for psychiatry residents and medical
			students, as well as students in health administration,
			child care, chaplaincy, nursing, occupational therapy,
			pharmacy, psychology, social work and speech therapy. Many
			of these training programs are accredited by national and
			international bodies. Information regarding the training
			programs can be obtained from the individual
			disciplines.</P>
			
		<TR VALIGN=BOTTOM><TD>
			<TD><P><A NAME="continuing_education"><IMG ALT="Continuing Education of Mental Health Professionals" SRC="../images/continuing_education.gif" WIDTH=384 HEIGHT=26></A></P>
			<TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=60>
			
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P>Our goal is to be the primary Canadian centre for
			continuing mental health education. Currently we offer
			continuing education in the form of conferences, workshops,
			courses and one-week summer training institutes. Some of
			this training is designed for specific disciplines while
			most is multidisciplinary. The courses and workshops are
			targeted to the Toronto region, however, the conferences and
			institutes attract professionals from across Canada, the
			United States and Europe. Information about upcoming events
			is available by calling the Education Office at (416)
			979-6852 or by e-mail:
			<A HREF="mailto:educate@cs.clarke-inst.on.ca">educate@cs.clarke-inst.on.ca</A></P>
			
		<TR VALIGN=BOTTOM><TD>
			<TD><P><A NAME="public_education"><IMG ALT="Public Education" SRC="../images/public_education.gif" WIDTH=302 HEIGHT=26></A></P>
			<TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=60>
					
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P>Each year the
			<A HREF="../about_the_clarke/social_work.html#sw_family_program">TIPS
			program</A> of the <A HREF="../about_the_clarke/social_work.html">Social
			Work Department</A> and the clinical divisions present 6 to
			8 public forums on a variety of topics of interest to the
			general public. The purpose of these presentations is to
			provide useful information about causes and treatments of
			mental illnesses, to help people understand changes in the
			system of care, and to provide support for people with
			mental illnesses and their families. These sessions are
			well-attended and each year reach nearly 2 000 people. In
			addition, our
			<A HREF="../about_services/special_services.html#beyond_cuckoos_nest">Beyond
			the Cuckoo's Nest</A> program is attended by over 3 000 high
			school students who gain a much clearer understanding of
			mental illnesses through their involvement.</P>
			
		<TR VALIGN=BOTTOM><TD>
			<TD><P><A NAME="staff_education"><IMG ALT="Staff Education" SRC="../images/staff_education.gif" WIDTH=302 HEIGHT=26></A></P>
			<TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=60>
			
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P>The Clarke Institute supports professional development and
			training for staff by providing bursaries and other
			financial awards.</P>
	
												
		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD COLSPAN=3><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=30>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD><P ALIGN=RIGHT>
				<A HREF="../contents.html"><IMG ALT="*" SRC="../images/back_button_wt.gif"
					WIDTH=154 HEIGHT=58 BORDER=0 HSPACE=8></A></P>
			<TD><P><I><A HREF="../contents.html">Back to Main Contents</A></I></P>
		</TABLE>
	</BODY>
</HTML>
