	<HEAD>
		<TITLE>The Clarke Institute: About The Clarke: Schizophrenia Division</TITLE>
		<LINK REV="made" HREF="mailto:dave@thom.com">
	</HEAD>

	<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#CC6600" ALINK="#FFFFFF" VLINK="#000000">
		<TABLE WIDTH=600 BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR VALIGN=TOP><TD COLSPAN=3>
			<H1><IMG ALT="Schizophrenia Division" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=169
					 SRC="../images/schizophrenia_division_h.gif"></H1>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=170 HEIGHT=20>
					 <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=345 HEIGHT=20>			
					 <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P>The Clarke's Schizophrenia Division was established
			in 1995 to serve as a regional, provincial and national
			Centre of Excellence for the study and treatment of
			schizophrenia.  The Division is committed to specialized
			research and education, as well as the provision of clinical
			care and services.</P>
			
			<P>The Division's research mission is to advance the
			understanding of the causes of schizophrenia and to develop
			treatments which will optimize outcome. Individuals
			receiving care in this division are offered the opportunity
			to participate in research studies. The research efforts of
			the Schizophrenia Division have also been greatly enhanced
			by strong collaborative efforts with our Positron Emission
			Tomography (PET) Centre. The effective collaboration of the
			PET team and the Schizophrenia Division promises to yield
			important insights into the brain abnormalities which
			underlie schizophrenia, as well as generate new approaches
			to pharmacologic treatment of schizophrenia.</P>
			
			<P>In addition to supporting graduate and postgraduate
			training of health professionals, the Division is committed
			to community outreach and public education. We welcome
			invitations to speak with interested community and/or
			hospital-based programs about issues related to
			schizophrenia.</P>
			
			<P>The Division has also developed new clinical services
			available on referral from physicians, community agencies,
			families, and individuals with schizophrenia. These programs
			and how to access them are described in <A
			HREF="../about_services/schizophrenia_division.html">About
			The Clarke's Services: Schizophrenia Division</A>.</P>


		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD COLSPAN=3><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=30>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD><P ALIGN=RIGHT>
				<A HREF="../contents.html"><IMG ALT="*" SRC="../images/back_button_wt.gif"
					WIDTH=154 HEIGHT=58 BORDER=0 HSPACE=8></A></P>
			<TD><P><I><A HREF="../contents.html">Back to Main Contents</A></I></P>
