	<HEAD>
		<TITLE>The Clarke Institute: About The Clarke's Services: Special Services</TITLE>
		<LINK REV="made" HREF="mailto:dave@thom.com">
	</HEAD>

	<BODY BGCOLOR="#FF9900" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#FFFFFF" ALINK="#FF9900" VLINK="#000000">
		<TABLE WIDTH=600 BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR VALIGN=TOP><TD COLSPAN=3>
			<H1><IMG ALT="Special Services" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=169
					 SRC="../images/special_services_h.gif"></H1>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=170 HEIGHT=20>
					   <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=345 HEIGHT=20>			
					   <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P><B><A NAME="beyond_cuckoos_nest">Beyond the Cuckoo's Nest</A></B><BR>
			979-4747 ext. 2569<BR>
			
			An interactive program of 1/2 day workshops for senior high
			school and college students to help them understand mental
			illnesses and reduce stigma experienced in society. Teachers
			may book a session for their class by calling in advance.</P>
			

			<P><B><A NAME="chaplaincy_services">Chaplaincy Services</A></B><BR>

			979-2221, Ext. 2355<BR>
			
			Requests by patients for pastoral care or information on any
			of the department's program may be made directly to the
			Chaplain or through staff, family and volunteers.
			&quot;Requests for Pastoral Services&quot; forms are to be
			found at each Nursing Station.</P>
			
			<P><B><A NAME="clarke_consulting_group">Clarke Institute Consulting Group</A></B><BR>
			979-6845<BR>
			
			Provides consultations to organizations on a fee-for service
			basis, to assist them in developing or improving mental
			health services. Consults can include policy analysis,
			operating or program reviews, evaluation studies and
			research or epidemiology studies for governments, hospitals,
			district health councils and other agencies.</P>
			
			
			<P><B><A NAME="college_street_secondary">College Street Secondary School</A></B><BR>
			979-4747 ext. 2229<BR>
			
			Under the auspices of the Toronto Board of Education, the
			School is available to referred Clarke clients wishing to
			continue their secondary schooling during or after their
			treatment.</P>
			
			
			<P><B><A NAME="community_advisory_panel">The Community Advisory Panel</A></B><BR>
			
			With representation from clients, families, community
			agencies, the academic community and multicultural
			populations, the Panel helps to assess community needs and
			concerns in the mental health field. The Panel receives
			suggestions and feedback from Clarke clients and community
			members.</P>
			
			</P>Write to the Chairperson c/o Room 819<BR>
			Clarke Institute of Psychiatry<BR>
			250 College Street<BR>
			Toronto, Ontario<BR>
			M5T 1R8.</P>
			
			
			<P><B><A NAME="community_linkage_program">Community Linkage Program</A></B><BR>
			979-6908<BR>
			
			This program develops linkages with consumer/survivor
			groups, family groups, community mental health services and
			government bodies, to share expertise and resources and work
			together on joint activities of mutual concern, especially
			activities relating to Mental Health Reform.</P>
			
			
			<P><B><A NAME="critical_incident_debriefing">Critical Incident Stress Debriefing</A></B><BR>
			979-4974<BR>
			
			These debriefings are offered by a team of staff to help
			individuals or groups cope with sudden, unexpected,
			stressful incidents - accident, violent event, or other. The
			service is available at no charge to the community; the team
			will travel to the site of the incident if appropriate.</P>
			
			
			<P><B><A NAME="family_program">Family Program</A></B><BR>
			979-4747 ext. 2576<BR>
			
			The Family Program operates support groups for relatives and
			family members, free TIPS forums (Taking Initiative in
			Psychiatric Settings) and booklets on mental illness for
			clients and families. The Family Advisory Group provides
			direction to Institute programs from the family members'
			point of view.</P>
			
			
			<P><B><A NAME="pharmacy_drug_info_line">Pharmacy Drug Info Line</A></B><BR>
			979-6802<BR>
			
			The Pharmacy provides a comprehensive drug service to
			patients of the Institute; operates a Drug Information Line
			to respond to professional and community enquiries about
			medications used in psychiatry; publishes a newsletter for
			professionals; and distributes a series of information
			booklets on various commonly-used medications.</P>
			
			
			<P><B><A NAME="work_adjustment">Work Adjustment and Employment Support Program</A></B><BR>
			979-6897<BR>
			
			Assists persons with significant mental health problems to
			enter and maintain employment and training. Vocational
			assessment, support and supervised placement at work
			stations in the community and at The Clarke are provided.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD COLSPAN=3><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=30>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD><P ALIGN=RIGHT>
				<A HREF="../contents.html"><IMG ALT="*" SRC="../images/back_button_yl.gif"
					WIDTH=154 HEIGHT=58 BORDER=0 HSPACE=8></A></P>
			<TD><P><I><A HREF="../contents.html">Back to Main Contents</A></I></P>
