			<TD><P><A NAME="community_linkage"><IMG ALT="Community Linkage Corner" SRC="../images/community_linkage.gif" WIDTH=302 HEIGHT=26></A></P>
			<TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=60>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P><B>New Information Service for Clarke Clients</B></P>

			<P>The Consumer/Survivor Information Resource Centre (C/S
			Info Centre) of Toronto is initiating a program at the
			Clarke Institute of Psychiatry aimed at providing
			information on mental health resources available in the
			broader community to clients of the Clarke.  These resources
			include information on housing, employment and advocacy
			services in the community.  The C/S Info Centre will be
			working in partnership with the Consumer Facilitator at the
			Clarke, in the new Consumer Facilitator and Information
			Centre on the ground floor of the Institute in Room G46A,
			ext 2729. Clients and staff of the Clarke are invited to
			drop in for an introduction to the services.  Chris
			Whittaker, the coordinator, is already known to some of us
			at The Clarke as he attends the discharge planning meeting
			in GPU and a similar meeting on the CIU. Chris will be open
			for business in October and will take the rest of this month
			getting aquainted with the Divisions. If you have any
			questions about this new C/S Info Centre/Clarke partnership,
			please call the C/S Info Centre at (416) 538-0203 or Dale
			Butterill at ext 6908. We welcome this initiative by the C/S
			Info Centre and expect it will enhance the lives of many
			Clarke clients.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=BOTTOM><TD>
			<TD><P><A NAME="chaplaincy"><IMG ALT="A Guide to Chaplaincy Services" SRC="../images/guide_to_chaplaincy.gif" WIDTH=302 HEIGHT=26></A></P>
			<TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=60>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P><B>Purpose</B></P>

			<P>The role of the Chaplaincy Department is predicated on
			the recognition of the fundamental importance of religion in
			the conduct of life. It strives to affirm the importance of
			the spiritual dimension related to patient's experience of
			illness and the &quot;wellness&quot; continuum.</P>
			
			<P><B>Chaplaincy believes that:</B></P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
				ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>It is important to affirm patients as unique
			individuals and respond to them with emphatic, unconditional
			love.</P>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
				ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>That it can make a useful contribution to patients by
			helping them to discover for themselves those spiritual
			truths which nourish the human spirit and foster health.</P>

			<P>Chaplaincy provides counselling, emotional and spiritual
			support to patients, their families and staff. A Pastor,
			Priest, Minister, Rabbi or faith leader of your choice may
			be contacted through the Chaplaincy Department.</P>			


		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD COLSPAN=3><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=30>
