<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//Netscape Comm. Corp.//DTD HTML//EN">

<HTML>

	<!--
		This HTML document was marked up by David Veldhuizen
		of HTM Interactive <http://www.thom.com/> or <dave@thom.com>
		Copyright 1996; all rights reserved.
	 -->

	<HEAD>
		<TITLE>The Clarke Institute: About Medication: Psychostimulants</TITLE>
		<LINK REV="made" HREF="mailto:dave@thom.com">
	</HEAD>

	<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#CC6600" ALINK="#FFFFFF" VLINK="#000000">
		<TABLE WIDTH=600 BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR VALIGN=TOP><TD COLSPAN=3>
			<H1><IMG ALT="Psychostimulants" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=169
			 SRC="../images/psychostimulants_h.gif"></H1>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=170 HEIGHT=20>
			 <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=345 HEIGHT=20>			
			 <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P>Psychostimulants are used to treat a number of conditions including:</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
				ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Attention Deficit Hyperactivity Disorders in children, adolescents and adults;</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
				ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Narcolepsy, a sleep disorder which results in attacks of sudden sleep during the day;</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
				ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Certain forms of Major Depression, where they can be used alone, or in combination with antidepressant drugs.</P>

		<P>Psychostimulant medications are known to be potent
		stimulants of both the central and peripheral nervous
		system, probably by affecting both dopamine and
		norepinephrine in the brain. This effect on brain chemicals
		likely explain why these medications work. Psychostimulants
		have been used by millions of people since being discovered
		in the 1960s.</P>
		
		<P>Clinical improvement may be gradual and benefits may not
		be evident for up to 4 weeks.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=170 HEIGHT=20>
			 <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=345 HEIGHT=20>			
			 <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P><B>Side Effects</B></P>

			<P>As with any other effective medication, unwanted side
			effects may develop. In most cases, these disappear as
			therapy is continued. Occasionally the dose may need to be
			reduced by your doctor.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=170 HEIGHT=20>
			 <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=345 HEIGHT=20>			
			 <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P><B>Side effects which should be reported to your
			doctor at the next appointment include:</B></P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
				ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Loss of appetite, weight loss -- Taking the medication after meals, eating smaller meals more frequently or drinking high calorie drinks may help.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
				ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Upset stomachs, nausea -- Taking the medication with food or milk may be useful.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
				ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Headache -- Mild analgesics may help. Have your blood pressure checked periodically while on these medications. A change in dose or timing may be useful.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
				ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Dry mouth -- Sour candy, sugarless gum, etc. can help increase salivation. Drink water and brush your teeth regularly.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
				ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Blurred vision -- Usually disappears over time (near vision only is affected).</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
				ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Energizing effect with excitability, nervousness, agitation.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
				ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Mild hair loss.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=170 HEIGHT=20>
			 <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=345 HEIGHT=20>			
			 <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P><B>Side effects which would be reported to your doctor as soon as possible include:</B></P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
				ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Insomnia, difficulty following asleep -- The doctor may suggest taking the drug earlier in the day, or may change the dose.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
				ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Muscle twitches, tics, movement problems.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
				ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Faster or irregular heart beat.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
				ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Persistent throbbing headache.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
				ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Unexplained skin rash, itchiness.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
				ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Soreness of the mouth, gums or throat.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
				ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Flu-like symptoms.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
				ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Dark-coloured urine.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
				ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Yellow tinge in the eyes or to the skin.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
				ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Easy bruising, bleeding, appearance of splotchy purplish darkening of skin.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=170 HEIGHT=20>
			 <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=345 HEIGHT=20>			
			 <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P><B>Conditions to report immediately to your doctor:</B></P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
				ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Severe agitation or restlessness.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
				ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>A switch in mood to an unusual state of happiness or irritability; fluctuations in mood.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
				ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Finding out you are pregnant.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=170 HEIGHT=20>
			 <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=345 HEIGHT=20>			
			 <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P><B>Precautions</B></P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
				ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Use caution while driving or performing tasks requiring alertness as these drugs can mask symptoms of fatigue and impair coordination.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
				ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Stimulants may interact with other prescribed medication, so inform all physicians you see that you are taking this medication.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
				ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Abrupt withdrawal after prolonged use can result in insomnia and changes in mood and behaviour.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=170 HEIGHT=20>
			 <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=345 HEIGHT=20>			
			 <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P><B>Other Instructions</B></P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
				ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Take your medication exactly as prescribed; do not increase the dose without the physicians knowledge.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
				ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Do not chew or crush the tablets or capsules.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
				ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Report to your doctor any changes in sleeping or eating habits, or changes in mood or behaviour.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
				ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Check with your doctor or pharmacist before taking other drugs including over-the-counter cold remedies or decongestants.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
				ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>If you miss a regular dose by 3 hours or less, take the dose when you remember it. If more than 3 hours have elapsed, skip the missed dose and resume your normal schedule. Never double up doses on your own.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
				ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>If you have any questions, do not hesitate to contact either your doctor, nurse or pharmacist.</P>

			<P>Prepared by the Pharmacy Department<BR>
			Clarke Institute of Psychiatry<BR>
			Form #268 (Dec '95)</P>
							
		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD COLSPAN=3><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=30>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD><P ALIGN=RIGHT>
				<A HREF="../contents.html"><IMG ALT="*" SRC="../images/back_button_wt.gif"
			WIDTH=154 HEIGHT=58 BORDER=0 HSPACE=8></A></P>
			<TD><P><I><A HREF="../contents.html">Back to Main Contents</A></I></P>
