<HTML>

	<!--
		This HTML document was marked up by David Veldhuizen
		of HTM Interactive <http://www.thom.com/> or <dave@thom.com>
		Copyright 1996; all rights reserved.
	 -->

	<HEAD>
		<TITLE>The Clarke Institute: About Medication: Carbamazepine</TITLE>
		<LINK REV="made" HREF="mailto:dave@thom.com">
	</HEAD>

	<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#CC6600" ALINK="#FFFFFF" VLINK="#000000">
		<TABLE WIDTH=600 BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR VALIGN=TOP><TD COLSPAN=3>
			<H1><IMG ALT="Carbamazepine" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=169
			 SRC="../images/carbamazepine_h.gif"></H1>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=170 HEIGHT=20>
			 <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=345 HEIGHT=20>			
			 <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>
		
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P>The medication you are taking is called Carbamazepine.
			Carbamazepine has traditionally been used to treat epilepsy
			and trigeminal neuralgia. It has also been found useful in
			the treatment of mood disorders, where a person's mood
			changes from a depressed feeling to a high feeling, or vice
			versa. When taken regularly as prescribed, carbamazepine
			helps control these mood swings and usually helps prevent
			further episodes, in the majority of patients. It has been
			found helpful in patients whose mood swings occur frequently
			and in those patients who do not respond to lithium
			carbonate.</P>
			
			<P>The dose of carbamazepine is different for every patient
			based on the amount of drug in the blood. Blood samples are
			regularly taken to make sure that the dose is neither too
			high nor too low.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=170 HEIGHT=20>
			 <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=345 HEIGHT=20>			
			 <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>
		
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P><B>Side Effects</B></P>

			<P>As with any other effective medication, unwanted side
			effects may develop. The nature and timing of side effects
			differ from person to person; many side effects will
			decrease with time. It is important to continue taking your
			medication unless told to do otherwise by your
			physician.</P>
			
			<P>COMMON SIDE EFFECTS which may occur during the early part
			of your treatment and which should be reported to your
			doctor at the NEXT APPOINTMENT include:</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
			ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Dizziness -- get up from a lying or sitting position slowly. Dangle your legs over the edge of the bed for a few minutes before getting up. Sit or lie down if dizziness occurs.</P>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
			ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Drowsiness -- this effect usually goes away with time. Avoid driving a car or operating machinery if drowsiness occurs. Alcohol, sedatives, antihistamines (cold &amp; hay fever medication) will worsen the problem.</P>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
			ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Ataxia or unsteadiness on the feet.</P>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
			ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Blurred vision -- usually disappears in about 1 week (Near vision usually is affected.) Reading under a bright light or at a distance, or wearing reading glasses may help. If the problem is severe, the doctor may prescribe eye drops.</P>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
			ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Tremor.</P>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
			ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Gastrointestinal disturbances (upset stomach) -- taking the drug with food may alleviate some of the problem.</P>
		
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=170 HEIGHT=20>
			 <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=345 HEIGHT=20>			
			 <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>
		
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P><B>SIDE EFFECTS which should be reported IMMEDIATELY to your doctor include:</B></P>
		
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
			ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Soreness of the mouth, gums or throat; mouth lesions.</P>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
			ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Easy bruising, bleeding, appearance of splotchy purplish darkening of skin.</P>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
			ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Fever or flu-like symptoms.</P>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
			ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Profound weakness.</P>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
			ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Skin sensitivity reactions, rashes.</P>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
			ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Confusion.</P>
		
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=170 HEIGHT=20>
			 <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=345 HEIGHT=20>			
			 <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>
		
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P><B>CONDITIONS to report IMMEDIATELY to your doctor include:</B></P>
		
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
			ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Finding out you are pregnant.</P>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
			ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Deciding you are going to nurse your baby.</P>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
			ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Recurrence of mood changes.</P>
		
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=170 HEIGHT=20>
			 <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=345 HEIGHT=20>			
			 <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>
		
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P><B>Precautions</B></P>

			<P>Carbamazepine may interfere with medication prescribed by
			a physician. Please inform all physicans that you are taking
			carbamazepine.</P>
			
			<P>Medications which have been reported to interact with
			carbamazepine include:</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
			ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Antibiotics, e.g. erythromycin, doxycycline.</P>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
			ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Birth control pills.</P>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
			ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Asthma drugs, e.g. theophylline.</P>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
			ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Fluoxetine.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=170 HEIGHT=20>
			 <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=345 HEIGHT=20>			
			 <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>
		
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P><B>OTHER INSTRUCTIONS:</B></P>

			<OL>
				<LI>Take your carbamazepine exactly as prescribed.
				<LI>This medication may impair the mental and physical abilities required for driving a car or operating other machinery.
				<LI>Carbamazepine may enhance the effects of alcohol making you more sleepy, dizzy and lightheaded.
				<LI>Check with your doctor before taking other drugs, including over-the-counter medications such as cold remedies, etc.
				<LI>Carbamazepine may interact with medication used by a dentist, so let him know the name of the drug you are taking.
				<LI>Do not store in humid conditions (e.g. bathroom medication cupboards) as this drug can lose its potency and effectiveness.
			</OL>

			<P>IF YOU HAVE ANY QUESTIONS, DO NOT HESITATE TO CONTACT
			EITHER YOUR DOCTOR, PHARMACIST OR NURSE.</P>
			
			<P>Form #278
			November 1990</P>
																			
		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD COLSPAN=3><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=30>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD><P ALIGN=RIGHT>
				<A HREF="../contents.html"><IMG ALT="*" SRC="../images/back_button_wt.gif"
			WIDTH=154 HEIGHT=58 BORDER=0 HSPACE=8></A></P>
			<TD><P><I><A HREF="../contents.html">Back to Main Contents</A></I></P>
		</TABLE>
