<DOCHDR>
http://cip.clarke-inst.on.ca:80/about_medication/antiparkinsonian.html 192.197.205.222 19970121060459 text/html 7686
HTTP/1.0 200 OK
Server: Netscape-Communications/1.12
Date: Tuesday, 21-Jan-97 06:01:33 GMT
Last-modified: Friday, 06-Dec-96 21:45:37 GMT
Content-length: 7496
Content-type: text/html
</DOCHDR>
<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//Netscape Comm. Corp.//DTD HTML//EN">

<HTML>

	<!--
		This HTML document was marked up by David Veldhuizen
		of HTM Interactive <http://www.thom.com/> or <dave@thom.com>
		Copyright 1996; all rights reserved.
	 -->

	<HEAD>
		<TITLE>The Clarke Institute: About Medication: Antiparkinsonian Agents</TITLE>
		<LINK REV="made" HREF="mailto:dave@thom.com">
	</HEAD>

	<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#CC6600" ALINK="#FFFFFF" VLINK="#000000">
		<TABLE WIDTH=600 BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR VALIGN=TOP><TD COLSPAN=3>
			<H1><IMG ALT="Antiparkinsonian Agents" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=169
			 SRC="../images/antiparkinsonian_h.gif"></H1>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=170 HEIGHT=20>
			 <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=345 HEIGHT=20>			
			 <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>
		
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P>This medication is used to treat muscle side effects that
			some patients experience when they are being treated with
			neuroleptics (antipsychotics or major tranquilizers).</P>
			
			<P>Some of the muscle side effects which may be relieved by
			antiparkinsonian agents include:</P>
			
			<P><OL>
				<LI>Muscle spasms or contractions (e.g. in the neck or the eyes);
				<LI>Muscle rigidity, tremor or shuffling gait;
				<LI>Restlessness or 'nervous pacing';
				<LI>Muscle weakness, or a decrease or slowing of movement.
			</OL></P>
			
			<P>Most of the above side effects can be treated
			successfully with antiparkinsonian agents. Sometimes these
			drugs have to be given by injection for a quicker effect.
			Symptoms generally disappear within a few days. After 2 to 3
			weeks of treatment, the antiparkinsonian agent can be
			stopped to see if the muscle symptoms recur. If they do not,
			then the antiparkinsonian agent can be discontinued.</P>
			
			<P>Examples of antiparkinsonian agents include Cogentin,
			Kemadrin, Artane, Disipal, Symmetrel, Parsitan and
			Benadryl.</P>
		
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=170 HEIGHT=20>
			 <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=345 HEIGHT=20>			
			 <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>
		
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P><B>Side Effects</B></P>
		
			<P>MOST SIDE EFFECTS ARE USUALLY NOT SERIOUS OR TROUBLESOME.
			THEY WILL RESPOND TO APPROPRIATE TREATMENT, AND WILL
			DECREASE OR DISAPPEAR WITH TIME.</P>
			
			<P>Common side effects from anticholinergic agents include:</P>
		
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
			ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Drowsiness and lethargy -- this problem goes away with time. Avoid driving a car or operating machinery if drowsiness occurs. Alcohol, sedatives, antihistamines (cold and hayfever medication) will worsen the problem.</P>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
			ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Dry mouth -- sour candy, sugarless gum, etc., can help increase salivation. Drink water and brush your teeth regularly. Try to avoid sweet, calorie-laden beverages.</P>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
			ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Constipation -- increase bulk foods in diet (bran, salads, etc.), drink plenty of fluids and exercise more often. If necessary, a bulk laxative (e.g. Metamucil, Fibyrax) can be used.</P>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
			ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Blurred vision -- this usually disappears in about a week. (Near vision usually is affected.) Reading under a bright light or at a distance may help; occasionally a magnifying glass can be useful. If the problem is severe, the doctor may prescribe eye drops.</P>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
			ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Nausea or heartburn -- if this happens, take your medication with food.</P>
		
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=170 HEIGHT=20>
			 <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=345 HEIGHT=20>			
			 <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>
		
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P><B>SIDE EFFECTS which should be reported IMMEDIATELY to
			your doctor include:</B></P>
		
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
			ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Disorientation and confusion;</P>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
			ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Worsening of your psychotic symptoms;</P>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
			ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Muscle weakness;</P>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
			ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Skin rash;</P>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
			ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Persistent constipation;</P>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
			ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Inability to urinate.</P>
		
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=170 HEIGHT=20>
			 <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=345 HEIGHT=20>			
			 <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>
		
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P><B>CONDITIONS which should be reported AS SOON AS
			POSSIBLE include:</B></P>
		
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
			ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Finding out you are pregnant;</P>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><IMG SRC="../images/bullet.gif"
			ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=5 HEIGHT=5 VSPACE=2 HSPACE=2 ALT="*">
			<TD><P>Deciding you are going to nurse your baby.</P>
		
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=170 HEIGHT=20>
			 <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=345 HEIGHT=20>			
			 <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>
		
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P><B>Other PRECAUTIONS to take:</B></P>
		
			<OL>
				<LI>This drug may impair the mental and physical abilities required for driving a car or operating other machinery.
				<LI>This drug may increase the effects of alcohol, making you more sleepy, dizzy and lightheaded.
				<LI>Avoid exposure to extreme heat and humidity since this drug may affect your body's ability to regulate temperature.
				<LI>Check with your doctor before taking other drugs, including over-the-counter medications such as cold remedies, etc.
				<LI>Do not increase your dose without consulting with your doctor.
			</OL>
			
			<P>IF YOU HAVE ANY QUESTIONS, DO NOT HESITATE TO CONTACT
			EITHER YOUR DOCTOR, NURSE OR PHARMACIST.</P>
			
			<P>Form #277 May/92</P>
													
		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD COLSPAN=3><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=30>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD><P ALIGN=RIGHT>
				<A HREF="../contents.html"><IMG ALT="*" SRC="../images/back_button_wt.gif"
			WIDTH=154 HEIGHT=58 BORDER=0 HSPACE=8></A></P>
			<TD><P><I><A HREF="../contents.html">Back to Main Contents</A></I></P>
		</TABLE>
