	<HEAD>
		<TITLE>The Clarke Institute: About The Clarke: General Psychiatry Division</TITLE>
		<LINK REV="made" HREF="mailto:dave@thom.com">
	</HEAD>

	<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#CC6600" ALINK="#FFFFFF" VLINK="#000000">
		<TABLE WIDTH=600 BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR VALIGN=TOP><TD COLSPAN=3>
			<H1><IMG ALT="General Psychiatry Division" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=169
					 SRC="../images/psychiatric_division_h.gif"></H1>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=170 HEIGHT=20>
					   <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=345 HEIGHT=20>			
					   <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P>The General Psychiatry Division provides a wide array of
			inpatient and outpatient services for adults suffering from
			mental illnesses. It also serves as a major training ground
			for medical students, residents in psychiatry, and other
			mental health professions students. Finally, it provides a
			setting for research to improve the understanding and
			treatment of mental illnesses.</P>
			
			<P>The clinical staff of the General Psychiatry Division
			includes 8 full-time psychiatrists, 19 part-time
			psychiatrists, six resident psychiatrists, five social workers, two
			occupational therapists, two psychologists, a speech
			pathologist, and a large complement of nurses.</P>
			
			<P>The clinical services of the General Psychiatry Division
			include: the
			<A HREF="../about_services/general_psychiatry.html#emergency_department">Emergency
			Department</A>, where approximately 3,000 assessments are
			carried out per year; the
			<A HREF="../about_services/general_psychiatry.html#emergency_followup">Emergency
			Follow-up Clinic</A>, which takes crisis referrals from the
			emergency room, other sources within the Institute, and the
			community; the
			<A HREF="../about_services/general_psychiatry.html#assessment_clinic">Assessment
			Clinic</A>, which provides consultation to health
			professionals in the community; the
			<A HREF="../about_services/general_psychiatry.html#high_risk_consultation">High
			Risk Consultation Clinic</A>, which offers focal
			consultation on persons who are suicidal; the
			<A HREF="../about_services/general_psychiatry.html#deafness_clinic">Deafness
			Clinic</A>, which specializes in psychiatric problems of the
			hearing-impaired; and the
			<A HREF="../about_services/general_psychiatry.html#psychotherapy_centre">Psychotherapy
			Centre</A>, which focuses on assessment and referral of
			individuals specifically seeking psychotherapy.</P>
			
			<P>The
			<A HREF="../about_services/mood_and_anxiety.html#interpersonal_therapy">Interpersonal
			Therapy Clinic</A>, co-sponsored by the
			<A HREF="../about_services/mood_and_anxiety.html">Mood and
			Anxiety Disorders Division</A>, offers a research-based form
			of short-term psychotherapy to appropriate individuals.
			Inpatient services include a
			<A HREF="../about_services/general_psychiatry.html#acute_care_inpatient">General
			Psychiatry Unit</A> which accommodates many emergency
			admissions and an
			<A HREF="../about_services/general_psychiatry.html#acute_care_inpatient">Acute
			Care Unit</A> which features a high level of nursing care in
			an extremely safe setting.</P> 			

			<P>Throughout the Division, staff work in interdisciplinary
			teams using a biopsychosocial approach with a focus on brief
			and effective interventions delivered in a compassionate and
			evidence-based manner. There are no barriers to access to
			the clinical services by virtue of gender, culture,
			diagnosis, or type of treatment indicated. This provides not
			only a broad array of services but also an excellent
			learning opportunity for students. Areas of research within
			the Division relate to education, psychotherapy, suicide,
			interdisciplinary team functioning, and cognitive
			functioning related to outcome after hospitalization.</P>

			<P>Information about these activities can be found in the
			section on <A HREF="../about_research/index.html">Research at the Clarke</A>.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD COLSPAN=3><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=30>
