			<I>McGill, 1991</I><BR>
			Research and practical experiences have spanned various
			areas, including clinical, social, counselling, and
			educational psychology. Interested in working with
			different groups of children (e.g., those with learning
			disabilities, behavioral and socioemotional difficulties). 
			Work, to date, has focused primarily on psychological
			testing, and consultation with family, school, and other
