			of sexual assaults against children and assertiveness
			training. Research interests include the effect on
			clinicians of working with sex offenders.</P>
			
			<P>Sherri MacKay, Ph.D.<BR>
			<I>University of Toronto, 1985</I><BR>
			Current work is in juvenile arson, delinquency, parent-child
			relationships, and childhood deafness. Research and
			clinical interests include developmental psychopathology,
			hearing impaired children, parent-child interactions, and
			fire setting.</P>
			
			<P>David Nussbaum, Ph.D.<BR>
			<I>University of Waterloo, 1983</I><BR>
			Clinical interests include assessment of personality
			disorders and neuropsychological impairment. Research
			interests consist of the use of the SCID Personality
