			<P>Kenneth J. Zucker, Ph.D.<BR>
			<I>University of Toronto, 1982</I><BR>
			Clinical and Research interests include gender identity
			disorders in children and adolescents; attachment and child
			psychopathology; risk factors in child psychopathology;
			developmental psychopathology; individual child
			psychotherapy; parental counselling.The Institute is
			responsible for conducting clinical research, offering
			clinical service and teaching mental health professionals
			and others. It is a training centre for all mental health
			disciplines. Students have access to a wide variety of
			lectures, seminars, and symposia. The Psychology Department
			follows a scientist- practitioner orientation. Placements
			for PhD candidates are available in both research and
			clinical areas. The library is well stocked and computer and
			audio-visual resources are excellent.</P>
			
												
