			<I>York University, 1971</I></P>
			
			<P>Meagan Smith, PhD<BR>
			<I>State University of New York at Stony Brook, 1993</I></P>
			
			<P>Brenda B. Toner, PhD<BR>
			<I>University of Toronto, 1983</I></P>
			
			<P>Percy Wright, PhD<BR>
			<I>York University, 1992</I></P>
			
			<P>Arlene Young, PhD<BR>
			<I>University of Waterloo, 1993</I></P>
			
			<P>Kenneth J. Zucker, PhD<BR>
			<I>University of Toronto, 1982</I></P>

			<P><B>Acceptance and Notification Procedures</B></P>
			
			<P>In selecting interns The Clarke Institute follows the
			Association of Psychology and Postdoctoral Internship
			Center's (APPIC) voluntary guidelines. Applicants are
			notified no earlier than 9:00 A.M. Central Standard Time on
			the second Monday in February. Those applicants must respond
			no later than 12:00 noon Central Standard Time the following
			day.</P>
			
			<P>Alternate applicants accepted between 9:00 A.M. Monday
			and 12:00 noon Tuesday may be asked to respond by Tuesday
			noon Central Standard Time, but not earlier. Applicants
			accepted after Tuesday noon should be prepared to make a
			quick decision, on the assumption that they have already
			considered previous offers.</P>
			
			<P>Applicants whom The Clarke does not intend to offer
			positions to will be notified no later than the first Monday
			in February. Alternate applicants will be notified of their
			status, but not before 9:00 A.M. of the second Monday in
			February.</P>
			
			<P>The Clarke Institute sends copies of all letters
			confirming internship positions to the directors of training
			of those students who have accepted internship positions.
			Any offer from The Clarke IS CONTINGENT UPON THE APPLICANT
			NOT HAVING MADE A PRIOR COMMITMENT. Applicants are not to
			retain more than one offer at a time. The Clarke Institute
			reserves the right to withdraw an offer if it is determined
			that an applicant is holding more than one offer at a
			time.</P>
			
			<P>Applicants will be informed if any positions have been
			pre-allocated. Applicants, agencies, and programs are urged
			to report any violations of these guidelines to the
			Chairperson, APPIC Executive Committee.</P>
			
			<P><A HREF="faculty.html">Psychology Internship Faculty</A></P>
												
