	<HEAD>
		<TITLE>The Clarke Institute: About The Clarke's Services: Schizophrenia Division</TITLE>
		<LINK REV="made" HREF="mailto:dave@thom.com">
	</HEAD>

	<BODY BGCOLOR="#FF9900" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#FFFFFF" ALINK="#FF9900" VLINK="#000000">
		<TABLE WIDTH=600 BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR VALIGN=TOP><TD COLSPAN=3>
			<H1><IMG ALT="Schizophrenia Division" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=169
					 SRC="../images/schizophrenia_division_h.gif"></H1>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=170 HEIGHT=20>
					   <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=345 HEIGHT=20>			
					   <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P><I>The Schizophrenia Division provides clinical
			services on referral from physicians, community agencies,
			families, and individuals with schizophrenia.</I></P>
			
			<P><B><A NAME="referrals">Referrals</A></B></P>
			
			<P>Referrals can be made by family practitioners, community
			agencies, family members who are seeking assistance for
			relatives, community psychiatrists, or general hospital
			psychiatrists.  Individuals may also refer themselves. At
			the end of the treatment period, individuals will be
			directed back to their referring service provider for
			follow-up.</P>
			
			<P>Individuals referred to the Division will receive an
			initial evaluation. Following consultation, the opportunity
			to participate in a time-limited treatment which may include
			medical intervention, case management, supportive therapy,
			vocational counselling and family support may be offered.</P>

			<P>For further information, please contact:</P>
			
			<P>April Collins, MSW, CSW, Clinical Services Coordinator, Schizophrenia Division<BR>
			tel: (416) 979 4747 ext. 2549; fax: (416) 979 6849<BR>
			<A HREF="mailto:acollins@clarke-inst.on.ca">acollins@clarke-inst.on.ca</A></P>
			
			<P><B><A NAME="first_episode_psychosis_program">First Episode Psychosis Program</A></B><BR>
			Referrals: Kathy Ryan, RN, MSC(N)<BR>
			tel: (416) 979 4747 ext 2433, fax: (416) 979 6849</P>

			<P><I>For Urgent Admissions after regular hours: call (416)
			979 2221, and ask for First Episode staff on call to be
			paged.</I></P>
			
			<P>This program has been developed to meet the needs of
			individuals experiencing a first episode of psychosis.
			Getting help in the early stages of illness is critical.
			This program assists individuals and their families in the
			initial critical period of recovery and adjustment. People
			can be referred as outpatients to the assessment clinic or
			to the acute inpatient unit. The program is not appropriate
			for individuals who are experiencing a mood disorder, such
			as depression or mania, or a general medical condition
			considered to be the cause of their psychosis. Priority will
			be given to individuals who have not yet received any
			antipsychotic treatment and are between the ages of 18 and
			45 years.</P>

			<P><B><A NAME="schizophrenia_treatment_optimization_program">Schizophrenia Treatment Optimization Program (STOP)</A></B><BR>
			Referrals: April Collins, MSW, CSW<BR>
			tel: (416) 979 4747 ext. 2549; fax: (416) 979 6849</P>

			<P>The STOP program provides multidisciplinary assessment,
			treatment and psychosocial intervention to optimize outcomes
			for individuals and their families over a period of six
			months to one year. The multi- disciplinary team will work
			in close collaboration with the referral source during the
			treatment period to organize appropriate services and
			resources to facilitate long-term adjustment within the
			community. A specialized Women's Program is available to
			investigate and treat the specific biological and
			psychosocial needs of women with schizophrenia.</P>

			<P><B><A NAME="medication_assessment_program_for_schizophrenia">Medication Assessment Program for Schizophrenia (MAPS)</A></B><BR>
			Referrals: April Collins, MSW, CSW<BR>
			tel: (416) 979 4747 ext. 2549; fax: (416) 979 6849</P>

			<P>The MAPS program offers rapid out-patient medication
			consultation including assessment of side effects, treatment
			resistance and neuroleptic-induced movement disorders.
			Individuals may be offered access to new pharmacological
			treatments which are currently being evaluated.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD COLSPAN=3><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=30>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD><P ALIGN=RIGHT>
				<A HREF="../contents.html"><IMG ALT="*" SRC="../images/back_button_yl.gif"
					WIDTH=154 HEIGHT=58 BORDER=0 HSPACE=8></A></P>
