	<HEAD>
		<TITLE>The Clarke Institute: About The Clarke's Services: Mood and Anxiety Division</TITLE>
		<LINK REV="made" HREF="mailto:dave@thom.com">
	</HEAD>

	<BODY BGCOLOR="#FF9900" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#FFFFFF" ALINK="#FF9900" VLINK="#000000">
		<TABLE WIDTH=600 BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR VALIGN=TOP><TD COLSPAN=3>
			<H1><IMG ALT="Mood and Anxiety Division" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=169
					 SRC="../images/mood_and_anxiety_h.gif"></H1>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=170 HEIGHT=20>
					   <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=345 HEIGHT=20>			
					   <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P><B><A NAME="depression_clinic">Depression Clinic</A></B><BR>
			979-6868<BR>
			
			This Clinic sees medically referred persons who have major
			depression or treatment-resistant depression, on an
			out-patient basis. The Clinic also offers a six week group
			program for partners or relatives of patients who have
			attended the Mood Disorders Program.</P>
			
			
			<P><B><A NAME="seasonal_affective_disorders">Seasonal
					Affective Disorders (SAD) Clinic</A></B><BR>
			979-6868<BR>
			
			The Seasonal Affective Disorders (SAD) Clinic conducts
			assessment and treatment of persons with seasonal affective
			disorder -- recurrent major episodes of depression which
			follow a seasonal pattern, for example, depression in
			winter.</P>
			
			
			<P><B><A NAME="bipolar_clinic">Bipolar Clinic</A></B><BR>
			979-6832<BR>
			
			This Clinic provides consultation, assessment, and in some
			cases, ongoing treatment for persons with Bipolar Mood
			Disorder (manic-depression). The Clinic also runs a support
			group for clients of the Bipolar and Mood Disorders clinics.</P>
			
			
			<P><B><A NAME="mood_disorders_inpatient">Mood Disorders Inpatient Unit</A></B><BR>
			
			This 18 bed inpatient unit provides assessment and treatment
			of persons with depressive or manic-depressive illness who
			require short-term hospitalization. In addition, there is a
			small unit for the treatment of persons with anxiety
			disorders, particularly obsessive-compulsive disorder.</P>
			
			
			<P><B><A NAME="day_treatment_program">Day Treatment Program</A></B><BR>
			979-4747 ext. 2434<BR>
			
			This six-week outpatient program gives persons with serious
			mood disorders intensive support and treatment on a day
			basis as an alternative to hospitalization. Referrals come
			from within The Clarke, particularly from the outpatient
			clinics in the Division as well as from caregivers in the
			community.</P>
			
			
			<P><B><A NAME="anxiety_disorders_clinic">Anxiety Disorders Clinic</A></B><BR>
			979-6819<BR>
			
			Conducts research into the nature and treatment of anxiety
			disorders, training in assessment and treatment of anxiety,
			and evaluations and treatment for disorders in which anxiety
			is the most prominent feature. These include panic disorder,
			specific phobias, obsessive compulsive disorder,
			posttraumatic stress disorder, acute stress disorders and
			generalized anxiety disorder. Both biological and
			psychological treatments are incorporated into outpatient
			care.</P>
			
			
			<P><B><A NAME="cognitive_behaviour_therapy">Cognitive
							Behaviour Therapy Unit</A></B><BR>
			979-4747 ext. 2628<BR>
			
			This outpatient service offers short-term cognitive therapy
			as a treatment for major depressive disorder. During
			individual or group therapy, clients explore and become
			aware of how attitudes, beliefs, expectations and thoughts
			can produce and maintain their depressed or anxious moods.</P>
			
			
			<P><B><A NAME="psychobiology">Psychobiology and Clinical
						Trials Research Unit in Anxiety</A></B><BR>
			979-6832<BR>
			
			Conducts research into causes of anxiety and related
			disorders and also offers assessment and treatment of
			persons with anxiety disorders including panic disorders,
			social phobia, post-traumatic stress disorder, generalized
			anxiety disorder and mixed anxiety depressions. Consults to
			health professional are also provided, in conjunction with
			the Anxiety Disorders Clinic.</P>
			
			
			<P><B><A NAME="interpersonal_therapy">Interpersonal Therapy Clinic</A></B><BR>
			Referrals: 979-6925<BR>
			
			Provides interpersonal psychotherapy, a relatively new form
			of brief psychotherapy. Individual treatment for persons
			suffering from depression, dysthymia and/or borderline
			personality disorder is offered for up to 16 sessions. This
			Clinic operates jointly between the Mood/Anxiety and General
			Psychiatry Divisions.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD COLSPAN=3><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=30>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD><P ALIGN=RIGHT>
