<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//Netscape Comm. Corp.//DTD HTML//EN">

<HTML>

	<!--
		This HTML document was marked up by David Veldhuizen
		of HTM Interactive <http://www.thom.com/> or <dave@thom.com>
		Copyright 1996; all rights reserved.
	 -->

	<HEAD>
		<TITLE>The Clarke Institute: About The Clarke's Services: Forensic Division</TITLE>
		<LINK REV="made" HREF="mailto:dave@thom.com">
	</HEAD>

	<BODY BGCOLOR="#FF9900" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#FFFFFF" ALINK="#FF9900" VLINK="#000000">
		<TABLE WIDTH=600 BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR VALIGN=TOP><TD COLSPAN=3>
			<H1><IMG ALT="Forensic Division" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=169
					 SRC="../images/forensic_division_h.gif"></H1>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=170 HEIGHT=20>
					   <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=345 HEIGHT=20>			
					   <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P><B>Referrals</B><BR>
			(416) 979-6833</P>
			
			<P><I>Provides assessment of individuals remanded by the courts,
			as well as treatment for some persons involved with the law,
			either currently or in the past. A multi-disciplinary team
			works with specific groups of offenders, chiefly sex
			offenders and the physically aggressive.</I></P>
						
			<P><B><A NAME="sexual_behaviour_clinic">Sexual Behaviour Clinic</A></B><BR>
			The Sexual Behaviour Clinic provides assessment,
			consultation, treatment, and community management of sex
			offenders. The assessment may include phallometric testing
			(a method for assessing the sexual preferences of males; see
			the <A HREF="#phallometric_lab">Phallometric
			Laboratory</A>),  psychological testing, and clinical
			interviews. Assessment and consultation for alleged or
			convicted sex offenders is occasionally provided to legal
			counsel or the courts. Treatment can include both individual
			and group therapy. Group therapy is organized in terms of
			content modules and is based on a cognitive-behavioural
			model of relapse prevention. Relapse prevention focuses on
			self-management and reduction of risk.</P>

			<P>Head: Robert Dickey, MD, FRCP(C)</P>

			<P>Intake Coordinator:	Shirley Broekstra, B.A., R.N.<BR>
			tel. (416) 979-4747, ext. 2638<BR>
			fax (416) 979-6965</P>

			<P><B><A NAME="anger_management_clinic">Anger Management Clinic</A></B><BR>
			The Anger Management Clinic provides assessment,
			consultation, and treatment for adults who have a history of
			impulsive, aggressive behaviour directed at other persons or
			property. Individuals are assessed by a multidisciplinary
			team regarding suitability for individual or group
			treatment. Although the clinic provides consultations to a
			broad range of individuals, the focus in treatment is on
			individuals with personality disorders.</P>

			<P>Head: Phillip Klassen, MD, FRCP(C)</P>

			<P>Intake Coordinator:	Claudia Van Duinen<BR>
			tel. (416) 979-4747, ext. 2304<BR>
			fax (416) 979-6965</P>

			<P><B><A NAME="impulse_control_disorders">Impulse Control Disorders Program</A></B><BR>
			Provides care to people with disorders of impulse control
			including explosive personality disorder, attention-deficit
			disorder and sexual disorders.</P>
			
			<P><B><A NAME="phallometric_lab">Phallometric Laboratory</A></B><BR>
			The Phallometric Laboratory provides a specialized
			psychophysiological assessment of male sexual preferences
			through measurement of changes in penile volume to various
			sexual stimuli. This assessment is provided mainly to sex
			offenders, but is also occasionally provided to men with
			questions or concerns about their noncriminal sexual
			behaviour. This laboratory is the oldest laboratory of its
			kind in North America, and is one of the most sophisticated
			in the world in terms of its technology and database. It is
			the only facility in a Metropolitan Toronto public hospital
			or clinic to provide this kind of assessment.</P>
			
			<P>Head: Phillip Klassen, MD, FRCP(C)</P>
			
			<P>Laboratory Coordinator: Michael Kuban, M.A.</P>
			
			<P>Intake Coordinator:	Shirley Broekstra, B.A., R.N.<BR>
			tel. (416) 979-4747, ext. 2638<BR>
			fax (416) 979-6965</P>

			<P><B><A NAME="gender_identity_clinic">Gender Identity Clinic</A></B><BR>
			The Gender Identity Clinic provides assessment and makes
			recommendations for patients referred for cross-dressing or
			gender dysphoria -- dissatisfaction with one's body combined
			with the desire to have the body of the opposite sex. The
			Clinic also offers expertise on the diagnosis of
			transsexualism, and counsels patients about the decision to
			undergo sex reassignment surgery. The Clinic is uniquely
			empowered by the Ontario Health Insurance Plan (OHIP) to
			approve reimbursement for sex reassignment surgery of
			diagnosed transsexual individuals; residents of some other
			provinces are also reimbursed by their provincial health
			plans following approval by this clinic.</P>
			
			<P>Head: Ray Blanchard, Ph.D., C.Psych</P>
			
			<P>Secretary:  Anne Bonotto<BR>
			tel. (416) 979-4747, ext. 2339<BR>
			fax (416) 979-6965</P>

			<P><B><A NAME="metro_forensic_service">Metropolitan Toronto
			Forensic Service (METFORS)</A></B><BR>
			(416) 535-8501 ext. 2962<BR>
			
			This medium secure unit,located at the Queen Street Mental
			Health Centre, carries out psychiatric assessment under a
			variety of provisions within the Criminal Code. The courts
			are the main source of referral. METFORS has a 23 bed
			inpatient unit, to which persons may be remanded for up to
			30 days. An outpatient Brief Assessment Unit operates three
			days a week.</P>

			<P><B><A NAME="police_liaison">Police Liaison and Investigative Support Program</A></B><BR>
			The Police Liaison and Investigative Support Program, in a
			joint initiative with the Metropolitan Toronto Police Force,
			provides police education in the form of a week long Crisis
			Resolution course at the Charles O. Bick Police College.
			This course provides training to police officers regarding
			mental illness, treatment and consultation resources
			available in the Metropolitan Toronto area, and effective,
			nonviolent intervention with individuals suffering from
			mental illness. Education on other topics is also provided
			to the Metro Toronto, Ontario, and Canadian police colleges.</P>
			
			<P>Investigative support is provided to Detective Operations of
			the Metropolitan Toronto Police, Criminal Investigative
			Branch of the Ontario Provincial Police, and the Violent
			Crime Analysis Branch of the Royal Canadian Mounted Police.</P>
			
			<P>Coordinator: Peter Collins, M.C.A., MD, FRCP(C)<BR>
			tel. (416) 979-6847<BR>
			fax (416) 979-6965</P>

			<P><B><A NAME="law_and_mental_health">Law and Mental Health Program</A></B><BR>
			The Law and Mental Health Program provides expertise and
			consultation on issues relating to mentally disordered
			offenders and the law, legislation pertaining to psychiatry
			and mental health services, psychiatry and the criminal
			justice system, competency, consent to treatment, and
			preventive detention. The Program also conducts research on
			issues in law and mental health.</P>
				
			<P>Senior Researcher: Alexander Greer, M.A., J.D.<BR>
			tel. (416) 979-6835<BR>
			fax (416) 979-6965</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD COLSPAN=3><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=30>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD><P ALIGN=RIGHT>
				<A HREF="../contents.html"><IMG ALT="*" SRC="../images/back_button_yl.gif"
					WIDTH=154 HEIGHT=58 BORDER=0 HSPACE=8></A></P>
			<TD><P><I><A HREF="../contents.html">Back to Main Contents</A></I></P>
		</TABLE>
