	<HEAD>
		<TITLE>The Clarke Institute: Family Court Clinic</TITLE>
		<LINK REV="made" HREF="mailto:dave@thom.com">
	</HEAD>

	<BODY BGCOLOR="#FF9900" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#FFFFFF" ALINK="#FF9900" VLINK="#000000">
		<TABLE WIDTH=600 BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR VALIGN=TOP><TD COLSPAN=3>
			<H1><IMG ALT="Family Court Clinic" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=169
					 SRC="../images/family_court_h.gif"></H1>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=170 HEIGHT=20>
					   <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=345 HEIGHT=20>			
					   <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P><B>Referrals</B><BR>
			979-4998</P>
			
			<P><I>The Family Court Clinic at The Clarke provides assessments,
			recommendations, and treatment services to children and
			families referred by judges of the Ontario Court of Justice
			(Provincial Division).</I></P>
			
			<P><B><A NAME="adolescent_program">Adolescent Program</A></B><BR>
			(416) 979-4998<BR>
			The Adolescent Program of Family Court Clinic deals
			primarily with referrals under the Young Offenders Act
			regarding antisocial youth, special education problems,
			juvenile offenders, and others.</P>
			
			
			<P><B><A NAME="child_welfare_program">Child Welfare Program</A></B><BR>
			(416) 979-4998<BR>
			This Family Court Clinic Program sees children and families
			where child neglect and abuse are of major concern. The
			Clinic receives referrals from legal counsel and Children's
			Aid Societies.</P>
			
			
			<P><B><A NAME="custody_and_access_program">Custody and Access Program</A></B><BR>
			(416) 979-4998<BR>
			Provides clinical assessment, recommendations, and where
			appropriate, treatment for families in dispute regarding
			custody and access issues, after separation or divorce of
			the parents. The Family Court Clinic specializes in helping
			families with special needs due to family violence,
			addictions, and personality difficulties.</P>
			
			
			<P><B><A NAME="for_kids_sake">For Kids' Sake</A></B><BR>
			(416) 979-4968<BR>
			For Kids' Sake is a preventive program for children aged 5
			to 14 whose parents are in severe conflict during or after
			divorce or separation. Participating families can be
			referred by family courts, the legal community, or mental
			health agencies. Consent and involvement of both parents is
			required.</P>
			
			
			<P><B><A NAME="arson_prevention">The Arson Prevention Program for Children (TAPP-C)</A></B><BR>
			(416) 979-3943<BR>
			TAPP-C is operated in collaboration with the Office of the
			Fire Marshal of Ontario and City of Toronto Fire Department,
			and provides assessment and fire safety education for
			children who are firesetters. Program staff provide training
			to assist other mental health and fire service professionals
			across the Province to implement TAPP-C in their
			communities.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD COLSPAN=3><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=30>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD><P ALIGN=RIGHT>
