	<HEAD>
		<TITLE>The Clarke Institute: About The Clarke's Services: Continuing Care Division</TITLE>
		<LINK REV="made" HREF="mailto:dave@thom.com">
	</HEAD>

	<BODY BGCOLOR="#FF9900" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#FFFFFF" ALINK="#FF9900" VLINK="#000000">
		<TABLE WIDTH=600 BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR VALIGN=TOP><TD COLSPAN=3>
			<H1><IMG ALT="Continuing Care Division" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=169
					 SRC="../images/continuing_care_h.gif"></H1>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=170 HEIGHT=20>
					   <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=345 HEIGHT=20>			
					   <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P><I>The Continuing Care Division serves individuals severely
			disabled by major mental illness, usually schizophrenia.</I></P>
			
			<P><B><A NAME="case_management_teams">Case Management Teams</A></B><BR>
			This Division operates on a psychosocial rehabilitation
			model. Each client is partnered with a case manager who
			provides support and coordinates treatment, training or
			community resources to help the individual recover, whether
			at home or in hospital.
			
			<P><B><A NAME="day_centre">Day Centre</A></B><BR>
			979-6904<BR>
			The Day centre provides skills training on a day basis to
			help continuing Care division clients enter into and
			function in the community.</P>
			
			<P><B><A NAME="first_episode">First Episode Psychosis Clinic</A></B><BR>
			979-6914<BR>
			Provides outpatient assessments for individuals presenting
			with a first psychotic episode.</P>
			
			<P><B><A NAME="health_systems_research">Health Systems Research Unit</A></B><BR>
			979-6845<BR>
			This Unit studies mental health service delivery and
			develops policy research and analysis aimed at improving
			delivery of mental health care. The Unit played a key role
			in the major population-based survey of mental illness in
			Ontario - which was published by the Ministry of Health as
			the Mental Health Supplement, as well as developing a series
			of policy research documents which have had a considerable
			influence on mental health reform in Ontario.</P>
			
			<P><B><A NAME="home_treatment">Home Treatment Program</A></B><BR>
			979-4747 ext. 2214<BR>
			Provides intensive home based care as an alternative to
			hospital admission, in partnership with the Home Care
			Program for Metropolitan Toronto (for Continuing Care
			Division clients who become acutely ill).</P>
			
			<P><B><A NAME="inpatient_care">Inpatient Care</A></B><BR>
			The Continuing Care Division operates a 30 bed Inpatient
			Program consisting of the Brief Hospitalization Program,
			which aims at rapid resolution of psychotic relapses, the
			Community Reintegration Program, which is designed to
			prepare clients for the transition from hospital to
			community; the Clinical Investigation Unit specializing in
			assessment and study of persons experiencing a first
			psychotic episode.</P>
			
			<P><B><A NAME="schizophrenia_relatives">The Schizophrenia Relatives and Friends Program</A></B><BR>
			979-4747 ext.2328<BR>
			This family support service holds weekly group sessions and
			open education forums for relatives and friends of
			individuals with schizophrenia.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD COLSPAN=3><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=30>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD><P ALIGN=RIGHT>
				<A HREF="../contents.html"><IMG ALT="*" SRC="../images/back_button_yl.gif"
					WIDTH=154 HEIGHT=58 BORDER=0 HSPACE=8></A></P>
			<TD><P><I><A HREF="../contents.html">Back to Main Contents</A></I></P>
