	<HEAD>
		<TITLE>The Clarke Institute: About The Clarke's Services: Child and Family Studies Division</TITLE>
		<LINK REV="made" HREF="mailto:dave@thom.com">
	</HEAD>

	<BODY BGCOLOR="#FF9900" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#FFFFFF" ALINK="#FF9900" VLINK="#000000">
		<TABLE WIDTH=600 BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD COLSPAN=3>
			<H1><IMG ALT="Child and Family Studies Division" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=169
					 SRC="../images/child_and_family_studies_h.gif"></H1>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=170 HEIGHT=20>
					   <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=345 HEIGHT=20>			
					   <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P><B>Intake Coordinator</B><BR>
			979-4747, ext.2255<P>
			
			<P><I>The Child and Family Studies Centre provides mental
			health services to families and children up to age 17.
			Referrals can be made by parents, physicians, schools and
			health facilities, except the ADHD and Psychopharmacology
			Clinics, to which patients must be physician-referred.</I><P>
			
			
			<P><B><A NAME="general_assessment_clinic">General Assessment Clinic</A></B><BR>
			
			The clinic provides assessment for children up to 17 years
			of age with a variety of emotional and behavioural problems
			including, but not limited to, anxiety disorders,
			depression, oppositional disorder, and difficulties related
			to illness, death, separation and sexual abuse.</P>
			
			
			<P><B><A NAME="adult_attention_deficit">Adult Attention Deficit
						Hyperactivity Disorders Program (ADHD)</A></B><BR>
			
			Persons referred are assessed and, if indicated, participate
			in an eight week psychoeducation group where they learn
			about ADHD and the medical, behavioural, and psychological
			approaches to the disorder.</P>
			
			
			<P><B><A NAME="child_at_risk_clinic">Child At Risk Clinic</A></B><BR>
			
			Provides assessment and therapy for children whose parents
			suffer from depression or manic-depression. Consultation to
			agencies and physicians, and group sessions for children and
			spouses are offered.</P>
			
			
			<P><B><A NAME="gender_identity_clinic">Child and Adolescent</A><BR>
			Gender Identity Clinic</B><BR>
			
			Assesses children and adolescents with gender identity
			problems, certain sexual concerns (e.g. transvestism) or
			conflicts regarding sexual orientation.</P>
			
			
			<P><B><A NAME="psychopharmacology_clinic">Child and Adolescent</A><BR>
			Psychopharmacology Clinic</B><BR>
			
			Offers consultation to medical professionals regarding
			medications for children or adolescents with psychiatric
			problems such as mood disorders, attention deficit
			hyperactivity disorder, obsessive-compulsive disorder and
			somatization problems. Referring physicians are provided
			with up to date literature and treatment information.</P>
			
			
			<P><B><A NAME="childrens_day_treatment">Children's Day Treatment Program</A></B><BR>
			
			Provides treatment for approximately 25 children between 5
			and 12 years of age whose emotional or behavioural problems
			prevent them being in regular school. Children attend a
			school program within the Centre taught by qualified Toronto
			Board teachers, and usually stay 1-2 years. Parents or
			guardians must work closely with the treatment team to
			ensure the treatment plan is implemented. Children attend
			daily but live with their families.</P>
			
			
			<P><B><A NAME="childrens_developmental">Children's Developmental</A><BR>
			Neuropsychiatry Clinic</B><BR>
			
			Assesses children with problems of speech and language
			development and/or academic failure which are accompanied by
			psychosocial problems including emotional/behavioural
			problems or psychiatric disorder. Clinic staff provide
			focused feedback to the referring source.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD COLSPAN=3><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=30>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD><P ALIGN=RIGHT>
				<A HREF="../contents.html"><IMG ALT="*" SRC="../images/back_button_yl.gif"
					WIDTH=154 HEIGHT=58 BORDER=0 HSPACE=8></A></P>
			<TD><P><I><A HREF="../contents.html">Back to Main Contents</A></I></P>
		</TABLE>
	</BODY>
