	<HEAD>
		<TITLE>The Clarke Institute: About The Clarke: Facts and Figures About The Clarke</TITLE>
		<LINK REV="made" HREF="mailto:dave@thom.com">
	</HEAD>

	<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#CC6600" ALINK="#FFFFFF" VLINK="#000000">
		<TABLE WIDTH=600 BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD COLSPAN=3>
			<H1><IMG ALT="Facts and Figures About The Clarke" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=169
					 SRC="../images/facts_h.gif"></H1>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=170 HEIGHT=20>
					   <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=345 HEIGHT=20>			
					   <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P>The Clarke Institute of Psychiatry opened in 1966 after
			the passage of the Ontario Mental Health Foundation Act
			created and mandated the Institute to &quot;maintain, manage
			and operate a hospital with facilities for psychiatric
			research, education, diagnosis and treatment.&quot; Read
			about The Clarke's background in <A HREF="history.html">A
			History of The Clarke</A>.</P>
			
			<P>The Institute operates as a fully-accredited public
			hospital with its own Board of Trustees. Members of the
			Board are appointed by provincial Order-in-Council, with one
			member elected by the medical staff (pursuant to the Public
			Hospitals Act), and two trustees nominated by the Ontario
			Mental Health Foundation. The Institute offers highly
			regarded inpatient and outpatient clinical programs in
			<A HREF="../about_services/child_and_family_studies.html">Child
			and Adolescent Psychiatry</A>,
			<A HREF="../about_services/mood_and_anxiety.html">Mood and
			Anxiety Disorders</A>,
			<A HREF="../about_services/schizophrenia_division.html">Schizophrenia</A>,
			and <A HREF="../about_services/psychiatry_division.html">General
			Psychiatry</A>. The majority of the funds to operate the
			hospital are provided by the Ontario Ministry of Health,
			with support from research grants and community
			donations.</P>
			
			<P>The Clarke has close ties with the University of Toronto.
			The Chairman of the University's Department of Psychiatry is
			also the President and Psychiatrist in Chief of the
			Institute. An agreement with the University recognizes the
			Institute as a fully accredited teaching hospital,
			permitting it to provide undergraduate and graduate medical
			education under the auspices of the faculty of Medicine. The
			Institute trains one quarter of the psychiatrists in Canada
			and half of those in Ontario. Formal training is also
			provided to students in nursing, psychology, social work,
			occupational therapy, pharmacy and child care work. Read
			<A HREF="../about_education/index.html">About Education</A>
			for more on The Clarke's educational programs. The Clarke is
			exceptional in that the entire faculty is focused on
			clinical and basic science psychiatric research.
			<A HREF="../about_research/index.html">About Research</A>
			describes the full range of Clarke research activities.</P>
			
		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=170 HEIGHT=20>
					   <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=345 HEIGHT=20>			
					   <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P><B>Officers</B></P>
			
			<P><I>Chairman, Board of Trustees</I><BR>
			Andrea Baumann<BR>
			Dip.RN, B.Sc.N., M.Sc.N., Ph.D.</P>
			
			<P><I>President &amp; Psychiatrist-in-Chief</I><BR>
			Paul E. Garfinkel, MD</P>
			
			<P><I>Executive Vice-President &amp; Chief Operating Officer</I><BR>
			Jean Simpson</P>
			
			<P><I>Vice-President Administration and Finance</I><BR>
			David J. Colgan, MA, MHSc</P>
			
			<P><I>Vice President Medical Affairs and Chief of Staff</I><BR>
			David S. Goldbloom, MD</P>
			
			<P><I>Vice-President Nursing</I><BR>
			Nancy E. Johnston, RN, MHSc</P>
			
			<P><I>Vice-President Professional Services</I><BR>
			Elizabeth Scott, MSc, BSCOT</P>
			
			<P><I>Vice-President Research</I><BR>
			Franco Vaccarino, Ph.D.</P>
			
			<P><I>Vice-President Education</I><BR>
			H. Bruce Ferguson, Ph.D., C.Psych</P>
			
			<P><I>Chairperson, Board of Directors of the Foundation</I><BR>
			Janice O'Born<BR>
			The Printing House Ltd.<BR>
			Charitable Office</P>
			
