	<HEAD>
		<TITLE>The Clarke Institute: Current Events: The Courage To Come Back Awards</TITLE>
		<LINK REV="made" HREF="mailto:dave@thom.com">
	</HEAD>

	<BODY BACKGROUND="../images/courage_logo.gif" TEXT="#000000"
		  LINK="#FF9900" ALINK="#FFFFFF" VLINK="#000000">
		<TABLE WIDTH=600 BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR VALIGN=TOP><TD COLSPAN=3>
			<H1><IMG ALT="Current Events" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=169
					 SRC="../images/current_events_h.gif"></H1></TR>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=170 HEIGHT=20>
					   <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=345 HEIGHT=20>			
					   <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD COLSPAN=3><P ALIGN=CENTER><B><IMG ALT="[Photo]"
			SRC="../images/courage_photo.gif" WIDTH=288 HEIGHT=175></B></P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P><B><IMG ALT="The Courage To Come Back Awards"
			SRC="../images/courage.gif" WIDTH=302 HEIGHT=26></B></P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P><B>1996 Campaign</B></P>
			
			<P>Each year, The Clarke Institute of Psychiatry
			Foundation holds its &quot;Courage to Come Back&quot;
			campaign under Honourary Co-chairs Paul Molitor and Silken
			Laumann. The campaign honours people throughout Ontario who
			have shown extraordinary courage in their recovery from
			illness, injury or addiction and helped the community.
			Proceeds from the campaign benefit The Clarke Institute of
			Psychiatry.</P>
			
			<P>The &quot;Courage To Come Back&quot; campaign provides
			dignity and recognition to people who have fought back
			against seemingly insurmountable odds and now serve as role
			models for those who are facing similar challenges. It
			allows the community to share in the lives of people who
			have overcome incredible challenges and in the process,
			helps us all appreciate what each of our own lives has to
			offer.</P>
			
			<P>The &quot;Courage&quot; campaign is unique in that it
			presents awards in seven different categories including:
			physical injury, general medical illness, chemical
			dependency, mental illness, youth, seniors and
			celebrity.</P>
			
			<P>The campaign relies totally upon the public who nominate
			friends, family members or colleagues for
			&quot;Courage&quot; awards. (Nominees must be residents of
			Ontario.) Nomination forms are available at all IDA Drug
			Stores and Printing House branches in Ontario or by calling
			The Clarke Foundation at (416) 979-6909. Deadline for
			nominations is October 4th, 1996.</P>
			
			<P>&quot;Courage&quot; awards are presented to seven
			courageous individuals during the awards dinner at the Inn
			on the Park in Toronto on November 21st. Seven hundred
			people including Paul Molitor and Silken Laumann are
			expected to attend.</P>
			
			<P>Tickets to the dinner at $125 are available by calling
			The Clarke Foundation at (416) 979-6909.</P>

			<P><B>Corporate Partners</B></P>
			
			<P>Bank of Montreal<BR>
			Barrick Gold Corporation<BR>
			Boiler Inspection &amp; Insurance Company<BR>
			Cott Corporation/Watt Design Group<BR>
			Swiss Bank Corp. (Canada)<BR>
			The Printing House Ltd.<BR>
			Toronto Blue Jays Baseball Club<BR>
			Sun Media Group</P>
			
			<P><B>Patrons:</B></P>
			
			<P>Blake Cassels Graydon<BR>
			C.I.B.C. Wood Gundy<BR>
			C.G. Management &amp; Communications<BR>
			Davies Ward Beck<BR>
			Ernst &amp; Young<BR>
			Goodman Phillips &amp; Vineberg<BR>
			Kellogg Canada Inc.<BR>
			Maclean Hunter Publishing Ltd.<BR>
			RBC Dominion Securities<BR>
			Royal Plastics Group<BR>
			Marvin Sherkin<BR>
			Ted Tremain<BR>
			United Messenger</P>
			
			<P><B>Underwriters</B></P>
			
			<P>V.I.P. Reception: Edward Bronfman</P>
			
			<P><B>Media Sponsor:</B></P>
			
			<P>The Toronto &amp; Ottawa Sun</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
