<HTML>

	<!--
		This HTML document was marked up by David Veldhuizen
		of HTM Interactive <http://www.thom.com/> or <dave@thom.com>
		Copyright 1996; all rights reserved.
	 -->

	<HEAD>
		<TITLE>The Clarke Institute: About The Clarke: Research Division</TITLE>
		<LINK REV="made" HREF="mailto:dave@thom.com">
	</HEAD>

	<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#CC6600" ALINK="#FFFFFF" VLINK="#000000">
		<TABLE WIDTH=600 BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR VALIGN=TOP><TD COLSPAN=3>
			<H1><IMG ALT="Research Division" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=169
					 SRC="../images/research_division_h.gif"></H1>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=170 HEIGHT=20>
					 <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=345 HEIGHT=20>			
					 <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P>At The Clarke, research is conducted across all
			clinical Divisions and takes many forms. Basic science
			research using state-of-the art technologies is aimed at
			learning about the body chemicals, genetic materials, or
			brain structures involved in psychiatric illnesses. Clinical
			research evaluates how specific treatments are working in
			practice. Qualitative methods are used to learn more about
			the subjective experience of clients with mental health
			problems. Community research surveys broad populations to
			provide information about the extent, nature, and severity
			of psychiatric disability, as the basis for providing
			services.</P>
			
			<P>Twelve sections within The Clarke's Research Division
			focus exclusively on research in the following areas:
			<A HREF="../about_research/index.html#biochemical_psychiatry">Biochemical Psychiatry</A>,
			<A HREF="../about_research/index.html#biopsychology">Biopsychology</A>,
			<A HREF="../about_research/index.html#culture_community_health">Culture, Community &amp; Health Studies</A>,
			<A HREF="../about_research/index.html#health_systems_research">Health Systems Research</A>,
			<A HREF="../about_research/index.html#human_neurochemical_pathology">Human Neurochemical Pathology</A>,
			<A HREF="../about_research/index.html#molecular_psychobiology">Molecular Psychobiology</A>,
			<A HREF="../about_research/index.html#neuroendocrinology">Neuroendocrinology</A>,
			<A HREF="../about_research/index.html#neuroimaging">Neuroimaging</A>,
			<A HREF="../about_research/index.html#positron_emission">Positron Emission Tomography</A>,
			<A HREF="../about_research/index.html#psychiatric_neurogenetics">Psychiatric Neurogenetics</A>,
			<A HREF="../about_research/index.html#transgenics_lab">Transgenics</A>, and
			<A HREF="../about_research/index.html#womens_mental_health">Women's Mental Health Research</A>.
			Each of these sections is described in detail in
			<A HREF="../about_research/index.html">About Research</A>.</P>
			
			<P>The twelve sections are affiliated with the University of
			Toronto's Departments of Psychiatry, Physiology,
			Pharmacology, Psychology, and Institute of Medical Sciences.
			This affiliation creates a rich environment for training at
			the graduate and post-graduate levels. The Research Division
			receives major sponsorship from the Medical Research Council
			of Canada, National Institutes of Health, Natural Sciences
			&amp; Engineering Research Council, Ontario Mental Health
			Foundation, and many other granting bodies. In addition, The
			Clarke actively seeks public, private, industry, and
			government involvement.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD COLSPAN=3><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=30>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD><P ALIGN=RIGHT>
				<A HREF="../contents.html"><IMG ALT="*" SRC="../images/back_button_wt.gif"
					WIDTH=154 HEIGHT=58 BORDER=0 HSPACE=8></A></P>
			<TD><P><I><A HREF="../contents.html">Back to Main Contents</A></I></P>
		</TABLE>
