<HTML>

	<!--
		This HTML document was marked up by David Veldhuizen
		of HTM Interactive <http://www.thom.com/> or <dave@thom.com>
		Copyright 1996; all rights reserved.
	 -->

	<HEAD>
		<TITLE>The Clarke Institute: About The Clarke: Pharmacy Department</TITLE>
		<LINK REV="made" HREF="mailto:dave@thom.com">
	</HEAD>

	<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#CC6600" ALINK="#FFFFFF" VLINK="#000000">
		<TABLE WIDTH=600 BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR VALIGN=TOP><TD COLSPAN=3>
			<H1><IMG ALT="Pharmacy Department" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=169
					 SRC="../images/pharmacy_h.gif"></H1>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=170 HEIGHT=20>
					   <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=345 HEIGHT=20>			
					   <TD><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=85 HEIGHT=20>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD>
			<TD><P>The Pharmacy Department provides comprehensive drug
			services and assists in promoting safe and appropriate drug
			therapy to all patients of the Institute. The Department
			consists of 5.5 pharmacists and 4.5 pharmacy assistants;
			secretarial support is provided through a part-time
			secretary.</P>
			
			<P>Pharmacists are involved with specific in-patient units
			within the Institute as members of multidisciplinary patient
			care teams. Their role includes evaluating medications
			ordered by physicians, monitoring drug dosage and drug
			interactions, and maintaining drug profiles on each patient.
			This monitoring identifies potential drug-related problems
			and helps in the resolution of issues that may be
			drug-related. The pharmacist attends multidisciplinary
			patient rounds to advise on drug therapy and acts as a
			resource for any drug-related concerns. A medication
			education group is offered weekly on each in-patient unit,
			to educate patients on their psychotropic medication and
			permit discussion of drug-related issues.</P>
			
			<P>The Out-patient Pharmacy evaluates, monitors and
			dispenses medication to eligible patients of the Institute.
			Education is provided on medication through individual
			counselling and provision of information pamphlets on
			specific drugs.</P>
			
			<P>Under the supervision of a pharmacist, pharmacy
			assistants are involved in all the purchasing and
			distributive functions of the Department. They order,
			control, prepare and dispense all medications distributed by
			the Pharmacy to in-patients, utilizing the unit-dose
			distribution system, and to out-patients.</P>
			
			<P>The Pharmacy acts as a resource in all drug-related
			research done at the Institute; pharmacists maintain,
			control and dispense investigational drugs. Audits and
			projects that evaluate the use of specific drugs are
			performed under the direction of the Pharmacy and
			Therapeutics Committee.</P>
			
			<P>Pharmacists provide drug information and education to
			staff, patients, outside professionals and the community
			through direct drug information requests and through the
			publication Pharmacy News, a bi-monthly newsletter that
			reviews current topics in psychotropic drug therapy.
			Pharmacists give presentations to professional and community
			audiences, on request.</P>
			
			<P>Three pharmacists are cross-appointed as tutors in the
			Faculty of Pharmacy at the University of Toronto and are
			involved in teaching clinical psychiatry to undergraduate
			students in the final year of the pharmacy program. The
			Pharmacy is a site for the elective rotation in psychiatry
			for postgraduate pharmacy students in the second year of the
			PharmD program at the University. A psychiatry rotation is
			also provided to pharmacists from other institutions, and to
			students from Ontario and from other provinces, on request.
			Students from various Pharmacy Assistant programs in the
			city are offered a training rotation in the Pharmacy.</P>

		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD COLSPAN=3><IMG ALT="" SRC="../images/spacer.gif" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=30>
		<TR VALIGN=TOP>
			<TD><P ALIGN=RIGHT>
				<A HREF="../contents.html"><IMG ALT="*" SRC="../images/back_button_wt.gif"
					WIDTH=154 HEIGHT=58 BORDER=0 HSPACE=8></A></P>
			<TD><P><I><A HREF="../contents.html">Back to Main Contents</A></I></P>
		</TABLE>
	</BODY>
